Set the background to a gray or ARGB color. <p> For the main drawing surface, the alpha value will be ignored. However, alpha can be used on PGraphics objects from createGraphics(). This is the only way to set all the pixels partially transparent, for instance. <p> Note that background() should be called before any transformations occur, because some implementations may require the current transformation matrix to be identity before drawing.
